Package edu.cnm.deepdive.passphrase.model

Class Passphrase

java.lang.Object
edu.cnm.deepdive.passphrase.model.Passphrase
public final class Passphrase extends Object
Represents a single passphrase, consisting of a name, a persistence key, and a list of words.

  • Method Details

    • append

      public boolean append(String word)
      Appends specified word to the end of the list of words in this passphrase. Since this method mutates the list of words in the passphrase, a list will be created first (if it doesn't already exist).
      Parameters:
      word - String to append to passphrase.
      Returns:
      true if word was successfully added, false otherwise.

    • insert

      public boolean insert(String word)
      Inserts specified word at the start of this passphrase. Since this method mutates the list of words in the passphrase, a list will be created first (if it doesn't already exist).
      Parameters:
      word - String to insert in passphrase.
      Returns:
      true if word was successfully inserted, false otherwise.

    • insert

      public boolean insert(int position, String word) throws IndexOutOfBoundsException
      Inserts specified word at index position in this passphrase.
      Parameters:
      position - index at which word is inserted in passphrase.
      word - String to insert in passphrase.
      Returns:
      true if word was successfully inserted, false otherwise.
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - if position is negative or greater than passphrase length.

    • remove

      public String remove(int position) throws IndexOutOfBoundsException

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      String word removed.
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - if position is negative or greater than or equal to passphrase length.
